Is it just me, or has @Google’s @GoogleMaps gone bad? 

It used to be I could quickly see restaurants around my location, but now it only shows a few major ones, not the one I’m in. 
#FirstWorldProblem when need to think rather than have #GoogleMaps tell you where to go!  pic.twitter.com/gz20n9OkGu
checking back again, would love to know what you're doing about this issue @googlemaps https://support.google.com/maps/thread/4134508?hl=en …

Frustrated about how GTFS (transit data standard) deals with big stations. This is Waterfront in Van. Instead of showing how long to walk from Expo to SeaBus, it assumes 0 minutes to go anywhere in station. Imagine how many connections have been missed!

@googlemaps @transitapppic.twitter.com/oZC4UO64qp

Problem is often that destinations aren't entered exactly correct, especially if just using a pin drop. If that doesn't solve problem, it can be reported and they will likely update navigation. Transit or not,  @lyft and @Uber do want you to get to your destination.
Second, a quick @googlemaps search got me to the overpass entrance to your example @trimet MAX station. @lyft uses google maps navigation, so it should get you there no problem.

@googlemaps Hi, I have a question. I updated the Google map app recently and I got a trouble that I can't use the label on the map. I really liked it and relayed on a lot to dig new places that I found in the city. I need it. How can I fix it? I am iPhone user.

Then we contacted to #Google support they corrected our address manually but it is not showing on @googlemaps and other details are still in pending. They said there is some problem in GMB at Google end. #GoogleMaps #DigitalMarketing #Digital

No need to debug my specific issue. It's a well-known problem with poor error messaging and slow key propagation, already reported in 2013 and still not fixed: https://stackoverflow.com/a/27463201/911298 …

I think it is a classic fail fast strategy. At times it is important to validate before. They made sure you noticed the logos and they made sure it worked smoothly :) 
Business 1, UX 1, Aesthetics soon 0 <

those logos look bad but are also almost illegible at that size. 

The simple icons are much easier to recognize —
Especially as many situations under which you use a map in your phone, you are likely also busy, distracted and in a hurry.
